<TITLE> Denmark to give $66m to upgrade ZIA </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 6 (bdnews24.com)  Denmark will provide Bangladesh close to $ 66 million for upgrading of Zia International Airport, according to an agreement signed on Thursday. Economic Relations Division (ERD) secretary Mohammad Musharraf Hossain Bhuiyan and Danish ambassador in Bangladesh Einar Hebogaard Jensen signed the agreement. The two-year project is for improvement of taxiways, drainage, radar, navigation and radio communication systems at ZIA. "With the money given by Denmark the taxiway of the airport will be re-carpeted and modernised, and primary and secondary radars would be set up," Civil Aviation Authority of Bangladesh chairman Air Commodore Sakeb Iqbal Khan Majlish told bdnews24.com. He said the project would be implemented in next two years under the supervision of civil aviation authorities. Denmark will give 50 percent of the sum as grant and the rest as loan, he added. bdne
